<item>
            <title>[WFMP-1] The start goal should allow an option to keep the process running</title>
                <link>https://issues.jboss.org/browse/WFMP-1</link>
                <project id="12316025" key="WFMP">WildFly Maven Plugin</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently with the &lt;tt&gt;start&lt;/tt&gt; goal the process is destroyed when maven exits. There should be an option to keep the process running after maven starts.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Some consideration needs to be given to what to do with the console output. The plugin would own the thread which consumes the console output. It&apos;s likely not a good option for the process to inherit the I/O streams from maven process. Something will need to be done otherwise buffer overflow errors may be seen.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12567389">WFMP-1</key>
            <summary>The start goal should allow an option to keep the process running</summary>
